{
    # Dedicated (cheaper) model for background memory compression.
    "llm_config": {
        "class": "anthropic",
        "model_name": "claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
        "temperature": 0.1
    },

    "metadata": {
        "description": "Compresses a conversation transcript into a compact, factual memory summary.",
        "tags": ["memory", "compression", "internal"]
    },

    "tools": [
        {
            "name": "compressor",
            "function": {
                "description": "Fold a conversation (and any prior summary) into an updated compact memory."
            },
            "instructions": """
You are a memory compressor. You are given an optional PRIOR SUMMARY and a batch of
newer conversation turns between a user and their assistant "Neura".

Produce an UPDATED memory summary that merges the prior summary with the new turns.

Preserve, in this priority order:
- Durable facts the user stated about themselves, their work, and preferences.
- Decisions made and their rationale.
- Named entities (projects, people, files, tools) and how they relate.
- Open tasks / things to follow up on.
- Key answers Neura gave that may be referenced later.

Drop: greetings, chit-chat, redundant restatements, and anything ephemeral.

Output ONLY the updated summary as terse bullet points grouped under short headers
(Facts, Decisions, Entities, Open items). No preamble, no closing remarks. Keep it
under ~250 words.
""",
            "command": "Compress the conversation into an updated memory summary."
        }
    ]
}
